  "text": "Two well-known criteria )i.e. detection accuracy and specificity) are used for nodule detection assessment, as suggested in [CITATION_1] . These criteria are functions of some simpler metrics such as True Positive (TP), False Positive (FP), False Negative (FN) and True Negative (TN) [CITATION_2] . The TP (TN) is the percentage of true nodules (true nonnodules) which have been correctly classified as nodules (non-nodules). Moreover, the FP (FN) is the percentage of true non-nodules (true nodules) which have been incorrectly classified as nodules (non-nodules). The detection accuracy is defined as [CITATION_3] ",
